snippet: A law firm hired by DraftKings found that although Ethan Haskell inadvertently released data about contestants’ lineups, he was unable to use that information to win money on the rival site FanDuel.
lead_paragraph: A law firm hired by DraftKings found that although Ethan Haskell inadvertently released data about contestants’ lineups, he was unable to use that information to win money on the rival site FanDuel.

headline.print_headline: Inquiry Finds No Wrongdoing by DraftKings Employee, the Company Says
